HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 186
BY REPRESENTATIVE MILLER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Hearts of Hope Children's Advocacy Center for its work in support of young
victims of abuse and trafficking.
WHEREAS, it is with great pride that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana recognizes Hearts of Hope Children's Advocacy Center (CAC) and
commends its work in support of young victims of abuse and trafficking; and
WHEREAS, Hearts of Hope CAC provides support services for youth, ages two to
seventeen, who are victims of sexual abuse, physical abuse, or trafficking or who witness
violent crimes; and
WHEREAS, Hearts of Hope CAC's services include forensic interviews and medical
exams, youth advocacy, and therapy; and
WHEREAS, Hearts of Hope CAC provides education on human trafficking and
provides training on care coordination and human trafficking screening tools; and
WHEREAS, Hearts of Hope CAC's prevention efforts include "I have a voice" and
the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children; and
WHEREAS, Lacey Pitre serves as the CAC coordinator and forensic service
manager, Audrie Outlaw and Kourtneii Henderson serve as regional care coordinators, Ann-
Marie Bourgeois serves as a CAC family and youth advocate, Cortney Sam serves as a
forensic interviewer and CAC family advocate, Makenzie Gallagher serves as a CAC case
tracker, and Melanie Foreman serves as a counselor and child and youth intervention
specialist; and
